race.comment: Competitive finish. Loved the win of HE'LL RIP (5) last start at Flemington in strong time, sitting off the pace and living up to his name when ripping home to score by 1.75 lengths. He seems to be appreciating having his racing spaced and a repeat of last start goes close. CATOGGIO (3) made the pace in the race won by HE'LL RIP first up at Flemington and stuck on quite well with the 61kg. He meets that horse better off now and will be fitter with Craig Williams going on from the inside gate. INNCOURT (12) is racing well in Sydney. Lane goes on and can figure. PRESSER (6) consistent gelding but hasn't won for a while. Put the writing on the wall last time over 1600m at Sandown-Hillside when second and beaten 1.5 lengths. Rates a hope.
